 store front politicians" who aimed to "give 'em hope" in his speeches. An illuminating introduction traces GLBTQ politics in San Francisco, situates Milk within that context, and elaborates the significance of his discourse and memories both to 1970s-era gay rights efforts and contemporary GLBTQ worldmaking.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aGay liberation movementxSourcesxHistoryx20th centuryxCaliforniaxSan Francisco. 0aGay liberation movementzCaliforniazSan FranciscoxHistoryy20th centuryvSources. 0aGay menxArchivesxCaliforniaxSan Francisco. 0aGay menxPolitical activityzCaliforniazSan FranciscoxHistoryy20th centuryvSources. 0aGay menxSourcesxPolitical activityxHistoryx20th centuryxCaliforniaxSan Francisco. 0aGay menzCaliforniazSan FranciscovArchives. 0aPoliticiansxArchivesxCaliforniaxSan Francisco. 0aPoliticianszCaliforniazSan FranciscovArchives. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh1 aBlack, Jason Edward, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMorris, Charles E., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520955028423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520955028.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles